###########################################################################################################
Initial setup(ssh to VB)
###########################################################################################################
1.mobaxterm installation in windows
2.making the network-adapter of VB-ubuntu as bridge-adapter
3.connecting through ssh from mobaxterm to VB-ubuntu

##########################################################################################################
Setting the git-github communication 
##########################################################################################################
1.create a github account and then give the following commands on the pc to save the account details:
        $ git config --global user.name "Sameekshshetty"
        $ git config --global user.email "sameeksh.ee17@bmsce.ac.in"
        $ git config --global core.editor vim
2.Take the clone of the github directory onto local machine
        $ git clone https://github.com/Sameekshshetty/IPC
3.Steps to be done to make the local changes reflect in github:
    3.1:Stage the changes
            $ git add file1.c
    3.2:Check the status of the file
            $ git status            or         $ git status -s
    3.3:Commit the changes
            $ git commit file1.c
    3.4:Now we can push the changes to the github
            $ git push origin main          or           $ git push origin master
    [Note:- In the place of password public-key has to be given (eg:- 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) 
     Note:- 'master' branch by default will not be present so we need to create it then do the step 3.4
     Note:- Before doing "push" command , "pull" should be done so that we are uptodate with github-repo
    ]
